Senate Resolution 74
By: Senators Hickman of the 4th, Gooch of the 51st, Kennedy of the 18th, Goodman of the
8th and Watson of the 11th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the interfaith organizations and volunteers involved in disaster
2 cleanup efforts; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia has faced numerous natural disasters that have caused
4 significant damage and hardship to its residents; and
5 WHEREAS, in times of crisis, communities come together to support one another,
6 demonstrating the strength and resilience of the human spirit; and
7 WHEREAS, interfaith and religious organizations and volunteers have played a crucial role
8 in disaster cleanup efforts, providing essential services, resources, and support to those
9 affected; and
10 WHEREAS, these interfaith efforts have fostered unity, understanding, and cooperation
11 among diverse religious communities, showcasing the power of collaboration and
12 compassion; and
